      <title>Critical Lifeburn AA</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Necromancers&amp;message.id=9845#M9845</link>
      <description>With clerics able to crit 32k, mages the same on summoned, wizards doing 42k (Ithink it's 42) for mana burn, is there any chance we might get a critical lifeburn AA next expansion?&amp;nbsp; We got the lowering of the reuse timer this time.&amp;nbsp; In its current form lifeburn is pretty much useless on modern bosses.&amp;nbsp; Hitting for the sum total of our HP makes it possible for 20k for the very few top people, and there would be several of us able to hit for 17k+, but really that is limited to a tiny few individuals playing the game.&amp;nbsp; The ability (not the chance, a definite ability) to critically lifeburn would make this class defining feature meaningful again.&amp;nbsp; I used to look forward to the necros all calling when their lifeburn recourse was off so the next one could go (back when we had more than 2 of us /mourn departed necros).&amp;nbsp; we don't really bother to call it now since we hardly ever use it, and when we do it's mostly at the very end of a raiding night, just to say that we actually could.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;It's depressing to see wizards regularly nuking 20k , and clerics preening themselves that they critted a turn undead for 32k on an undead when our largest possible damage is limited to our hp.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
