      <title>Damage Per Mana from PoR to TSS</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Necromancers&amp;message.id=9770#M9770</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;We got some new DPS spells in TSS, which was nice since we didn't get any in PoR.&amp;nbsp; And yes, some of the TSS DoTs even belong in the top 8 spell gems for DPS, though sadly a few others are worthless low dps or dpm spells.&amp;nbsp; Many necros have notived that they cannot cast for as long as they used to be able to, and complained, running oom on fights you didn't used to run oom on, because you are using TSS spells.&amp;nbsp; Well, it's apparent why, even with no foci at all our TSS spells have worse mana efficiency in the top 8 slots than prior expansion.&amp;nbsp; Add foci into the mix and the gap only widens.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We have a 17% increase in total damage for a 26% increase in mana costs which means efficiency went to hell, or for a nearly 7% loss.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;DoT duration in the top 8 went from an average 6.25 ticks down to 5.75 ticks. That means that we will have to cast more frequently on average, which additionally costs us more mana for the damage we are doing.&amp;nbsp; Add on top of that the fact that many necros had decent foci before tss, and lack it for tss spells, in addition to the loss of Affliction Efficiency (non raiders could have 25% mana pres to level 70 for DoTs), and you have quickly depleting mana pools.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Anywyas here's a comparison of Total Damage and DPM before any foci between our top 8 DoTs from PoR to TSS:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="http://img340.imageshack.us/img340/1852/tssdpmrk2ru4.jpg"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Fang of Death is left out of the PoR lineup due to it having a horrid dpm. Some necros may have used it regularly in their lineup pre-tss, but frankly I'd hope they were the minority. If you include Fang of Death we still have efficiency loss to TSS, but it's not quite as pronounced.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What to do?&lt;br&gt;1) Lower mana costs of TSS spells&lt;br&gt;2) Increase durations of TSS spells&lt;br&gt;3) Increase damage of TSS spells&lt;br&gt;4) Increase FT on Otherside by a decent amount&lt;br&gt;5) Any combination of the above 4&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
