      <title>Mana Regeneration in the Post-TSS Era: A Case Study</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Necromancers&amp;message.id=9768#M9768</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;U&gt;Mana Regeneration in the Post-TSS Era: A Case Study&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/U&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;Since the dawn of time, the necromancers have paid for their vastly superior mana regeneration with increased inefficiencies and reduced burst DPS. This tradeoff was generally regarded as fair and balanced by most. Wizards burst well, and necromancers used large mana regeneration to sustain well. Sustainability and burst power were juxtaposed, represented as the opposite ends of a continuum, if you will.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;B&gt;Today, the situation is thus:&lt;/B&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;U&gt;Wizard:&lt;/U&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Patient Harvest: 5800 mana every&amp;nbsp;6 minutes. This is&amp;nbsp;97 mana per tick for Rank 3. (Rank 2: 5625/70 = 80, Rank 1: 67)&lt;BR&gt;Familiar: 10 mana per tick.&lt;BR&gt;Scales of the Crystalwing (Rk III): 6 mana per tick (Rank 2: 5, Rank 1: 4)&lt;BR&gt;C. Pot (Type X): 14 mana per tick.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Total: 127 mana per tick, discounting meditation and non-class buffs, using all readily available self-cast buffs/potions.&lt;BR&gt;(Rank 2: 109, Rank 1: 95)&lt;BR&gt;Discounting potions:&lt;BR&gt;(Rank 3: 113, Rank 2: 95, Rank 1: 81)&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;U&gt;Necromancer:&lt;/U&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Otherside: 85 mana per tick (Rank 2: 81, Rank 1: 78)&lt;BR&gt;Wraithskin: 4 mana per tick (Does not vary by rank)&lt;BR&gt;Total: 89 mana per tick, discounting meditation and external buffs, using all readily available self-cast buffs/potions.&lt;BR&gt;(Rank 2: 85. Rank 1: 82)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Please note: Clarity potions do NOT stack with Lich, and are thus 100% useless to necromancers.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;As the above figures indicate, necromancers are now expected to be inferior to wizards across the board in terms of mana regeneration, while still paying the increased costs for their spells on every spell and generating reduced burst DPS as the tradeoff for sustainable DOT. In other words, we pay more on a spell-by-spell basis, to do less immediate damage. Due to the duration-based nature of our spells, it is typically more difficult (often impossible) to "dip" into OOC regen than for a similarly employed wizard, who can simply remain seated for the first half of combat to use up their combat-rest timer, and use superior burst DPS to "catch-up" after having sampled a couple of ticks of OOC.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;U&gt;Something is very, very askew here.&lt;/U&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;U&gt;Hypothesis:&lt;/U&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Otherside and Wraithskin need to have their mana regeneration components VASTLY increased, simply&amp;nbsp;to maintain the basic parity between in-combat regeneration rates. This basic analysis does not factor in any consideration about necromancer spell efficiency&amp;nbsp;being balanced around&amp;nbsp;superior mana regeneration spells (ie: Lich) that are not in evidence any longer.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Please note: I am not suggesting in any way that wizards are "above their station" or "overpowered". I am not suggesting any reduction in wizard ability, nor do I think such a thing is appropriate. I do, however, think that the natural order of the game has been altered (Inverted!) and needs to be set back into balance in this particular, by restoring necromancers to the apex of in-combat mana regen they have traditionally demonstrated.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I welcome discussion of this situtation, but I must request that we keep our discussion civil. If you have something constructive to add (like analysis of mana regeneration for other classes) you should feel free to do so. If you're only going to flame, save your breath for cooling your porridge, as I've donned Seasons for this encounter.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
